.TH "write_i2c_reg" 9 "write_i2c_reg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
write_i2c_reg \- writes to an internal i2c register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" write_i2c_reg
.BI "(void __iomem *addr "  ","
.BI "u8 index "  ","
.BI "u8 data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
dt3155 mmio base address
.IP "index" 12
index (internal address) of register to read
.IP "data" 12
data to be written
.SH "RETURN"
zero on success or error code
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function starts writing the specified (by index) register
and busy waits for the process to finish.
